cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC

The paper deals with the use of machine learning algorithms for the automatic detection of depression using multimodal features extracted from audio, visual, and text data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for text analysis, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. The use of visual data and the application of computer vision techniques such as Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM) clustering and Fisher vector approach suggest that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category. The use of Support Vector Machine (SVM) and neural networks for classification indicates that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with mental health and the impact of depression on individuals, which suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible sub-category.
